    <item>
      <title>Ansible Automation Platform Contents</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/ansible-automation-contents/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Apr 2026 06:56:11 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/ansible-automation-contents/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Disclaimer:&lt;/em&gt; These notes reflect my personal understanding and working thoughts on Ansible Automation Platform. They are not intended to serve as formal documentation or a step-by-step guide. That said, I hope they offer useful insights, spark ideas, or provide some value as you explore AAP on your own.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;adding-custom-collection&#34;&gt;Adding Custom Collection&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Create your custom collection&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ansible-galaxy collection init lab.webserver&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd lab/webserver/roles&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ansible-galaxy role init apache&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;roles/apache/task/main.yml&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34; data-lang=&#34;yaml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;---&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# tasks file for apache&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;- &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;ansible.builtin.dnf&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;httpd&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;state&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;present&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;- &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;ansible.builtin.service&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;httpd&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;state&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;started&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;enabled&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;yes&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;- &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;ansible.posix.firewalld&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;service&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;state&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;enabled&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;permanent&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;immediate&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;lab/webserver/galaxy.yml&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Local Lab Docker Squid</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/local-lab-squid/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 20:56:00 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/local-lab-squid/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;//localhost:1313/squid.png&#34; alt=&#34;Squid Proxy&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My home lab currently runs on a laptop using VirtualBox, with all my VMs configured on a &lt;code&gt;host‑only&lt;/code&gt; network so I can take the entire environment with me. The downside is that the VMs’ web services are only reachable from the laptop itself. If I want to work from another workstation and connect over SSH, I lose access to anything the VMs expose—HTTP and so on.&#xA;One workaround I explored was running a Docker‑based Squid proxy to bridge that gap&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ansible Automation Platform Execution Environment</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/aap-private-execution-environment/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 18:17:45 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/aap-private-execution-environment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Disclaimer:&lt;/em&gt; These notes reflect my personal understanding and working thoughts on Ansible Automation Platform. They are not intended to serve as formal documentation or a step-by-step guide. That said, I hope they offer useful insights, spark ideas, or provide some value as you explore AAP on your own.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;adding-remote-registry&#34;&gt;Adding Remote Registry&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Automation Hub &amp;gt; Remote Registries&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;//localhost:1313/ansible/rh-remote-registry1.png&#34; alt=&#34;Remote Registry&#34;&gt;&#xA;URL: &lt;a href=&#34;https://registry.redhat.io/ansible-automation-platform-25/&#34;&gt;https://registry.redhat.io/ansible-automation-platform-25/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Click &lt;code&gt;Sync Remote Registry&lt;/code&gt; then &lt;code&gt;Index execution environments&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;//localhost:1313/ansible/rh-remote-registry2.png&#34; alt=&#34;Remote Registry&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Go to &lt;em&gt;Automation Hub &amp;gt; Execution Environments&lt;/em&gt; it will show Execution Environments from registry.redhat.io&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Certificate Authority Server using EasyRSA</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/easy-rsa/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 17:51:45 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/ansible/easy-rsa/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;One of the prerequisite of my Ansible Automation Platform 2.5/2.6 lab environment was to configure a &lt;code&gt;local&lt;/code&gt; Certificate Authority.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;I&amp;rsquo;ve used my workstation running on LinuxMint to configure my Certificate Authority.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;installing-easyrsa&#34;&gt;Installing EasyRSA&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt update&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt install easy-rsa&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir ~/easy-rsa&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ln - /usr/share/easy-rsa/* ~/easy-rsa/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd ~/easy-rsa&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;./easyrsa init-pki&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;./easyrsa build-ca&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;copy-ca-certificate-to-the-clients&#34;&gt;Copy CA certificate to the clients&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;RHEL:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo cp /tmp/ca.crt /etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo update-ca-trust&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;creating-signing-and-certificate-requests&#34;&gt;Creating Signing and Certificate Requests&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To be done on the clients&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
